\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish the governance framework for the Elko County Information Operations Department's IT Asset Catalog and service level commitments.
 This policy defines the lifecycle status classifications governing IT support posture,
 the standards by which work orders are triaged and prioritized,
 and the response and resolution commitments the Department makes to County personnel and departments.
 It ensures that service delivery expectations are clearly defined,
 consistently applied,
 and auditably enforced across all asset types and support tiers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all hardware models,
 software titles,
 and services within the operational purview of the Information Operations Department,
 regardless of asset support tier as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 It governs all work orders submitted to the Department by County personnel,
 departments,
 or internal IT staff,
 and all vendor contracts or service agreements for IT-Supported and Vendor-Managed assets.
 This policy applies to all Information Operations personnel involved in triage,
 service delivery,
 escalation,
 and vendor coordination.
\end_layout

