\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall serve as the sole approving authority for the IT Asset Catalog and all lifecycle status classifications and reclassifications.
 Shall maintain the authoritative list of mission-critical systems eligible for after-hours on-call activation.
 Shall authorize extensions to Deprecated asset replacement deadlines in writing.
 Shall authorize continued remediation beyond the standard labor ceiling by written notation in the work order.
 Shall approve vendor SLA terms at contract execution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall ensure the IT Asset Catalog is maintained current in Redmine.
 Shall conduct lifecycle status classification reviews and prepare reclassification proposals for IT Director approval.
 Shall ensure triage is performed within required timeframes and that service level commitments are met across all active work orders.
 Shall monitor vendor SLA performance in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Shall maintain after-hours contact procedures and on-call rotation schedules in Redmine.
 Shall identify and document vendor SLA gaps in existing contracts and present them to the IT Director no later than ninety (90) days prior to each applicable renewal opportunity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Department Personnel (All Tiers)
\series default
:
 Shall perform triage on assigned work orders within the required window,
 confirming or reclassifying severity based on verified operational impact.
 Shall document all reclassifications,
 remediation attempts,
 escalation rationale,
 and closure decisions in the work order.
 Shall adhere to response and resolution commitments as defined in this policy.
 Shall refer work orders for Unsupported assets to the IT Director for disposition without performing remediation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
County Personnel and Department Heads
\series default
:
 Shall submit service requests through the designated work order system.
 Shall provide sufficient information at the time of submission to enable triage.
 Shall respond to pending information requests from IT staff within five (5) consecutive business days to prevent work order closure.
\end_layout

